==Timeline of tallest buildings and structures==
[[Image:Croydon tower.jpg|thumb|right|upright|An artist's impression of the Croydon Gateway Landmark Tower.]]
Croydon's skyline has been built up mostly since the mid-20th century. [[No.1 Croydon]] held the title of tallest structure in Croydon for 38 years until [[Altitude 25]] is built. Although by 2010 if all predictions in the timing of construction is correct, the [[Croydon Vocational Tower]] will take over the title only to be replaced by the [[Croydon Gateway|Croydon Gateway Landmark Tower]] a year later.<ref>{{cite web| title = London - Full Summary of Projects| publisher= Will Fox, SkyscraperCity.com| url=http://www.skyscrapernews.com/buildings.php?id=46| accessdate=2006-12-15}}</ref>
